  ---
  Model Architecture (models/groundingdino/model.py)

  GroundingDINO(nn.Module) — 5-stage pipeline:

  1. Backbone → TimmBackbone(name, out_indices=[1,2,3], pretrained, freeze_at=1) wraps a timm.create_model(..., features_only=True). Returns (features, out_masks) where features is
   a list of (B, C_i, H_i, W_i). ResNet50 gives channels [256, 512, 1024] at strides [8, 16, 32]. Mask convention: True = padded/invalid.
  2. Neck → FPN(in_channels=[256,512,1024], out_channels=256, num_levels=4). Top-down lateral merges for 3 levels + 1 extra stride-2 P6 level appended. All outputs are (B, 256,
  H_i, W_i).
  3. Input projection → ModuleList of 4 × [Conv2d(256→256,1), GroupNorm(32,256)], one per FPN level. Xavier-uniform init on conv weights.
  4. Position embeddings → PositionEmbeddingSine(num_pos_feats=128). CRITICAL: the current transformer.py signature is forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor — it takes
  only the feature map (ignores any mask). However model._build_masks_and_pos calls self.pos_embed(feat, m) passing a mask as a second positional argument. This is the known bug
  tracked in the notebook (produces TypeError: PositionEmbeddingSine.forward() takes 2 positional arguments but 3 were given). The fix is to update PositionEmbeddingSine.forward to
   accept mask=None as an optional second argument and use it if provided (or ignore it). The output is (B, d_model, H, W).
  5. Encoder → TransformerEncoder(6 × TransformerEncoderLayer). Operates on (total_HW, B, d_model) seq-first tensors (batch_first=False throughout). Each layer: self-attention with
   additive positional encoding on Q and K, followed by FFN + LayerNorm.
  6. Decoder → TransformerDecoder(6 × TransformerDecoderLayer, return_intermediate=True). Also seq-first. Each layer: self-attention on queries + cross-attention to encoder memory,
   FFN. Returns torch.stack(intermediates) of shape (num_layers, Q, B, C) — the GroundingDINO.forward post-processes this via the per-layer class/box heads.

  6. Note: TransformerDecoder in the current code does NOT have the box-refinement MLP heads inside it. Those are on GroundingDINO itself... Actually on closer reading the current
  TransformerDecoder returns raw feature tensors, and GroundingDINO has no explicit per-layer class/box heads defined in __init__. The current model builds the class head as a
  simple linear later applied to the decoder output. The current code uses all_logits, all_boxes = self.decoder(...) but TransformerDecoder.forward only returns one tensor (the
  stacked intermediates) — this is another mismatch to flag and fix.
  7. Output heads (on GroundingDINO): pred_logits: (B, Q, num_classes) and pred_boxes: (B, Q, 4) in normalised cx/cy/w/h.
  8. Reference points: nn.Embedding(300, 4) init uniform_(0.05, 0.95). In forward: .sigmoid().clamp(1e-4, 1-1e-4).
  9. build_model(cfg) — factory in model.py, assembles all submodules from config.
  10. Checkpoint I/O: save_checkpoint stores state_dict + backbone_name + num_classes + num_queries + epoch + metrics + cfg. load_checkpoint validates backbone/class compatibility
  before loading.

  ---
  Data Pipeline (training/dataset.py, training/transforms.py)

  COCODetectionDataset(Dataset):
  - Uses pycocotools.COCO to load annotations
  - Filters images with zero annotations
  - Remaps category IDs to contiguous 0-indexed labels
  - Images loaded via cv2 (BGR→RGB)
  - Box format INSIDE Albumentations: COCO [x, y, w, h] absolute. Box format RETURNED: normalised [cx, cy, w, h] in [0, 1]
  - Returns dict: {image, boxes, labels, image_id, orig_size, size}

  collate_fn: pads images to max (H, W) in batch. Returns {images, image_mask, targets, image_ids, orig_sizes, sizes}. Mask: False = valid pixel, True = padded.

  build_train_transforms(max_size=800): LongestMaxSize → PadIfNeeded(div32) → HorizontalFlip(p=0.5) → OneOfp=0.5 → OneOfp=0.2 → Normalize(ImageNet) → ToTensorV2

  build_val_transforms(max_size=800): LongestMaxSize → PadIfNeeded(div32) → Normalize(ImageNet) → ToTensorV2

  ImageNet stats: mean [0.485, 0.456, 0.406], std [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]

  ---
  Training Flow (training/trainer.py, training/losses.py)

  DetectionLightningModule(pl.LightningModule):
  - Builds GroundingDINO + HungarianMatcher + SetCriterion from config
  - configure_optimizers: AdamW with two param groups — backbone at 1e-5, rest at 1e-4, weight_decay=1e-4, MultiStepLR at epoch 40 ×0.1
  - setup(): probes dataset size, makes reproducible train/val split (seed=42, 80/20), creates two separate dataset instances with different transforms
  - _shared_step: forward → SetCriterion → log all losses including loss_total

  SetCriterion:
  1. Runs HungarianMatcher on final decoder output
  2. _loss_class: sigmoid focal over ALL (B, Q, num_classes) — matched queries get 1-hot target, unmatched get zeros (background)
  3. _loss_boxes: L1 + GIoU on matched pairs only. Uses _safe_box_for_giou to clamp degenerate boxes
  4. Repeats steps 1-3 for each aux decoder layer (named loss_ce_0..4, loss_bbox_0..4, loss_giou_0..4)
  5. Returns losses dict + loss_total (weighted sum using weight_dict)

  HungarianMatcher: fp32 cast, focal classification cost + L1 + GIoU, scipy.optimize.linear_sum_assignment per image. Fast path for empty GT batches. NaN guard on cost matrix.

  Weight dict (both final and all 5 aux layers): loss_ce=2.0, loss_bbox=5.0, loss_giou=2.0

  ---
  Inference Flow (inference/predictor.py, inference/postprocess.py)

  Predictor: loads checkpoint, wraps predict_image (single image) and evaluate (full COCO eval).

  - predict_image: val transforms → forward → threshold_filter(threshold=0.3, top_k=300) → apply_nms(iou=0.5) → scale boxes back to original pixel coords (xyxy absolute)
  - evaluate: DataLoader → batched forward → COCO result format → pycocotools.COCOeval → returns {mAP, mAP_50, mAP_75}

  threshold_filter: sigmoid logits → per-query max class score → threshold mask → top-k. Returns list of {scores, labels, boxes}.

  apply_nms: torchvision.ops.batched_nms (class-aware), boxes converted cxcywh→xyxy internally, returned in original cxcywh format.

  ---
  Known Bugs (active in the codebase at time of last notebook run)

  1. PositionEmbeddingSine.forward signature mismatch (the bug tracked in the notebook): transformer.py declares forward(self, x) (1 arg), but model._build_masks_and_pos calls
  self.pos_embed(feat, m) (2 args). Fix: add mask=None optional second argument to PositionEmbeddingSine.forward; use the mask when provided to derive not_mask instead of
  hardcoding all-ones.
  2. TransformerDecoder.forward returns a single tensor but GroundingDINO.forward unpacks it as all_logits, all_boxes = self.decoder(...). This means either there are missing
  class/box head MLPs on the decoder or on GroundingDINO that need to be wired up.
  3. batch_first=False throughout: fixed in current transformer.py — all nn.MultiheadAttention instances use batch_first=False. All tensors must be (seq_len, B, C) when entering
  encoder/decoder layers.
  4. Reference point init: fixed — nn.init.uniform_(self.reference_points.weight, 0.05, 0.95) prevents inverse_sigmoid from producing ±inf on the first forward pass.

