  ---
  Important Implementation Notes for Notebook Generation

  1. All imports use the actual module paths: from training.dataset import ..., from models.groundingdino.model import build_model, etc.
  2. sys.path.insert(0, str(ROOT)) must come before any project imports.
  3. The notebook runs without CUDA — the environment has torch 2.2.2+cpu. Use torch.no_grad() and downscale to 320×320 for the forward pass.
  4. num_workers=0 in the debug DataLoader — avoids multiprocessing issues in notebooks.
  5. The transformer module imports trigger a HuggingFace warning ("PyTorch was not found. Models won't be available...") — this is benign noise from a HuggingFace tokenizers
  side-import. The notebook should note this is expected.
  6. PositionEmbeddingSine must be called with 1 argument in the manual debug probe — model.pos_embed(projected) not model.pos_embed(projected, mask) — until the signature is
  fixed.
  7. Box coordinate conventions: Dataset/targets use normalised cx/cy/w/h. Visualisation converts to pixel x1/y1 for matplotlib. Inference converts to absolute x1/y1/x2/y2.
  8. Mask convention: False = valid pixel, True = padded (PyTorch MHA convention for key_padding_mask). The dataset collate_fn produces this. Inside model.forward, the mask is
  negated (~m) before being passed to MHA.








